# SECTION 7 — Complexity Extra Clarity

## How to Read Complexity — Step by Step Rules

### Rule 1 — Single statement = O(1)
```js
let x = 5;           // O(1)
let y = arr[3];      // O(1)
let z = a + b;       // O(1)
```

### Rule 2 — Single loop = O(n)
```js
for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
  console.log(i);    // runs n times → O(n)
}
```

### Rule 3 — Nested loops = O(n²)
```js
for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {       // n times
  for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {     // n times for each i
    console.log(i, j);              // n × n = O(n²)
  }
}
```

### Rule 4 — Loop that halves = O(log n)
```js
for (let i = n; i > 1; i = Math.floor(i / 2)) {
  console.log(i);    // n → n/2 → n/4 → ... → 1 = log n steps
}
```

### Rule 5 — Two separate loops = O(n) not O(2n)
```js
for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) { }   // O(n)
for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) { }   // O(n)
// Total = O(n + n) = O(2n) → drop constant → O(n)
```

## Complexity Quick Reference with Real Feeling

| Complexity | Name | n=10 | n=100 | n=1000 | Feel |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| O(1) | Constant | 1 | 1 | 1 | Instant always |
| O(log n) | Logarithmic | 3 | 7 | 10 | Almost instant |
| O(n) | Linear | 10 | 100 | 1000 | Grows with input |
| O(n log n) | Linearithmic | 30 | 700 | 10000 | Slightly heavy |
| O(n²) | Quadratic | 100 | 10000 | 1000000 | Gets slow fast |
| O(2ⁿ) | Exponential | 1024 | 💀 | 💀💀 | Unusable for large n |

