# SECTION 8 — Asymptotic Notations Extra Clarity

## The Three Notations — Simplified with One Example

**Example — Linear Search on array of n elements:**

```
Best case:  Element at index 0 → 1 step     → Ω(1)
Worst case: Element at last or not found → n steps → O(n)
Average:    Element somewhere in middle → n/2 steps → Θ(n)
```

## Visual Understanding

```
Time
 │                           O(n²) ← worst possible bound
 │                    O(n)   ← actual algorithm growth
 │             Θ(n)   ← tight bound (same as actual)
 │      Ω(1)   ← best possible bound
 │
 └──────────────────────────────── n (input size)

O  = ceiling — algorithm never goes ABOVE this
Ω  = floor   — algorithm never goes BELOW this
Θ  = when ceiling and floor are the same growth rate
```

## Common Algorithms — All Three Notations

| Algorithm | Ω (Best) | Θ (Average) | O (Worst) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Linear Search | Ω(1) | Θ(n) | O(n) |
| Binary Search | Ω(1) | Θ(log n) | O(log n) |
| Bubble Sort | Ω(n) | Θ(n²) | O(n²) |
| Merge Sort | Ω(n log n) | Θ(n log n) | O(n log n) |
| Quick Sort | Ω(n log n) | Θ(n log n) | O(n²) |
| Insertion Sort | Ω(n) | Θ(n²) | O(n²) |

