# SECTION 12 — Binary Search Using Recursion (Extra Clarity)

## Step by Step with Full Trace

**Array:** [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70] — Search for 50

```
binarySearch(arr, 50, 0, 6)
  low=0, high=6, mid=3 → arr[3]=40
  40 < 50 → search right half
  binarySearch(arr, 50, 4, 6)
    low=4, high=6, mid=5 → arr[5]=60
    60 > 50 → search left half
    binarySearch(arr, 50, 4, 4)
      low=4, high=4, mid=4 → arr[4]=50
      50 === 50 → FOUND at index 4!
```

## Code — Binary Search Using Recursion

```js
function binarySearch(arr, target, low = 0, high = arr.length - 1) {
  // Base case 1 — not found
  if (low > high) return -1;

  let mid = Math.floor((low + high) / 2);

  // Base case 2 — found
  if (arr[mid] === target) return mid;

  // Recursive case — search left or right half
  if (arr[mid] < target) {
    return binarySearch(arr, target, mid + 1, high); // go right
  } else {
    return binarySearch(arr, target, low, mid - 1);  // go left
  }
}

let arr = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70];
console.log(binarySearch(arr, 50)); // 4
console.log(binarySearch(arr, 25)); // -1
console.log(binarySearch(arr, 10)); // 0
console.log(binarySearch(arr, 70)); // 6
```

## Complexity
- **Time:** O(log n) — halves the array each call
- **Space:** O(log n) — log n stack frames in call stack

